parameters: Shopkeeper: "What's up? Another mission?"
Kru: "Yeah~. I want a break~"
Shopkeeper: "If you're going to rest, use our inn."
Innkeeper: "Staying the night, Kru?"
Kru: "Yeah, granny. I'd like to book two rooms..."
Innkeeper: "Unfortunately, we only have one room available."
Kru: "What! That's rare for you to be so fully booked..."

Innkeeper: "Quiet down. You're planning to lodge that young lady, right?
You can go back to the barracks."

Kru: "Well, that's the thing... it's a bit difficult for me to return to
the barracks now."

Umi: "Kru, we always sleep in the same room. You don't want to be with
Umi?"
Kru: "No! It's not like that but..."

Innkeeper: "Kru... The young lady says so too. Make up your mind and stay
in the same room."
Kru: "Granny..."
Innkeeper: "Oh, and I'll be charging for two people for the room."
Kru: "Ah, that's dirty!"
Umi: "Kru... Your language is bad. Apologize to the old lady."
Kru: "What, I'm the bad guy here!"
Innkeeper: "Oh, what a good girl. She's too good for you, Kru."
Umi: "Too good?"

Kru: "Ah, enough already. I'll call out when it's time to sleep! We're
going now!"
Innkeeper: "Alright, alright, thanks as always."
A
Shopkeeper: "Are you going to bed now?"
Yes
No
はい
Shopkeeper: "Don't stay up too late."
いいえ
Shopkeeper: "Alright, come again."
Innkeeper: "Did you sleep well?"
Kru: "No, not at all."
Umi: "Kru... couldn't you sleep?"
Kru: "Ah! No, no! I slept like a log."
Innkeeper: "Heh heh heh... Be grateful, young man!"
Kru: "Granny..."

Innkeeper: "By the way, since I gave you a discount on your stay last
night, could you run an errand for me?"
Kru: "Who gave me a discount?"

Innkeeper: "Eh? I'm sure I gave you a discount. Oh dear, getting old makes
one forgetful."
Kru: "Yeah yeah. So what am I supposed to buy?"
Innkeeper: "Please go buy some fruit from the market."
Kru: "Alright, alright. I'm on it."
"Go to the greengrocer. The greengrocer is in the northeast of the town."
Shopkeeper: "The market is to the east when you leave here."

Kru "This is terrible! Granny! The girl with me... she's been kidnapped by
bandits!"
Shopkeeper "What a disaster! We must go to her rescue at once!"
Kru "Ah! Granny! Do you know where the bandits' hideout is?"
Shopkeeper "I believe... I've heard rumors it's to the southeast of town."
Kru "Really? Thank you, Granny!"
B
Shopkeeper: "It's southeast of the town!"
